Rosey  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=splinterdaoc>Splinter DAOC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/18/03 2:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=640.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RvR experiences of Skalds</span><hr size=1> About a month ago I had one of the best experiences playing my skald... so much that it reminded me of the old days of running around the gorge.  Old schoolers remember what that was like.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I was wandering around Odin's for nearly an hour solo and unbuffed, and hadn't seen another person out there.  /sigh.  After a while of camping the amg I saw several feet coming through... so first instinct was to run and hide.  So I ran to the side of the mg and they ran through without seeing me.  It was three of them, 2 clerics (one RR6 the other RR4), and a wizard (RR2) who I'd never seen before.  Out of boredom of not finding anyone else to fight I decided to at least kill one of them before dying and get some rps for my time.<br>
<br>
I ran up behind them, and mez the RR4 cleric.  Woot.. it actually stuck.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Woot.. he didn't purge it.  The RR6 cleric who was leading ran about 15 ft further before she realized what was happening.  I jumped on the wizard, and managed to drop him in about 5 swings and two sets of DDs.. It was quite a bit of luck in that I resisted the clerics stun, and the wizard (ice) was actually a blue con (lvl 44) and had very little body resist and I was outdamaging her heals.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
After that I started to run away to savor my victory and get away alive.. but for some reason I went back to finish the fight.  I guess I was feeling suicidal; or afraid of the boredom of not finding another soul out in OG for the next hour.. still unsure.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I burn an endurance totem and run back to fight the two clerics.  The RR6 lands a stun on me which I immediately purged and in turn mezzed her.  Woot.. a second mez stuck.  Woot she didn't purge.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   At that time I start on the RR4 cleric.. Woot.. ZERO body resists!!!  I force him to use his instants.  Still no BoF.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Unfortunately the RR6 cleric became unmezzed before I could finish him off and she started smiting me and healing the other cleric.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I burned IP and stayed on the RR4 cleric, while interrupting the RR6 cleric with mez/snare/dd/dd.  She had burned her instants, and had started to rest to get power... I might actually get a second kill on the RR4.  I get him to around 5% life when she stands up to heal him.. I switch to her for one swing to ensure interrupting her, and then switch back to the RR4 for the killing blow.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   At this point I'm elated at my two kills and 1600 rps.<br>
<br>
For some reason the cleric decided to mez me at this time, burned MCL and rezzed the ice wizzie... who was kind enough to pbae me.  I thanked him with a swing of my axe and dropped him a second time.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   After that it was me and cleric, her with no instants, me with no end.  After a couple ablative procs I finished her off about another min later for another 1000 rps and with 30% life left.<br>
<br>
nerf skalds.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=clapperoth>Clapperoth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/18/03 4:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=640.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RvR experiences of Skalds</span><hr size=1> I had a similar experience last week in OG after the patch.  Ran into a trio of Hibs at the Albion Milegate who were watching the other way, a blademaster, eldrich and enchanter.  I mezzed the eldrich, took out the enchanter quickly while they were still surprised, then mezzed the blademaster and killed the eldrich.  I would almost have thought the eldrich was afk from it's low activity, but it seemed to try and cast a couple times.<br>
<br>
We've all had good experiences with casters though, so while this was a nice combination of events (surprise, plus mez working well) the real fun was that I hit FA II and downed an end potion just in time for the blademaster to come out of mez and engage me.  It was a medium length battle but I was able to beat him without using IP (he was of low realm rank and I'm RR6).  I camped the bodies for a few mins, and since they didn't release I went in search of their rezzer and found him (a bard, standing for some reason in the middle of the road) and did my job.<br>
<br>
Soloing for me has been exciting the last few weeks, but then I haven't done it in awhile so part of that is stretching mental muscles I haven't used in awhile.  I die often enough, but I've had some good victories.<br>
<br>
In groups, well...If I'm in a good group and successfully /assist the main melee damage dealer I do well, but otherwise I run into one of the old skald problems:  I often drive, so I'm the first one targeted by the enemy, and go down quickly.  Anyone in that situation generally does, but it's sometimes an instantanous thing. <p>Clapperoth Liefarg&lt;BR&gt;<br>
