</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mogabanar>Mogaba nar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/19/03 2:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=640.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RvR experiences of Skalds</span><hr size=1> I have had the opposite results of the above posters, most times I encounter other caster classes I’m often mezed before I can get in range to mez them, in both large scale as well as small scale events. With some of the new tactics of stun first and mez second this has been even worse on skalds I have seen many trying to fight on the fringe of battles now get mezed after being stuned. More and more we seem to be taxi’s to the fights, but once their we are fodder not getting heals. Quote “effective tanks need my heals” seems to be the healer catch for skalds and fighting on the fringe of battle because of less buffs from shaman of the same mind set does not help also. <br>
<br>
Now unlike the 2 above I don’t run solo, I don’t have a pocket buffer or healer I can use one account only, so I don’t travel alone, with scouts new skills it is hard not to run into a archer waiting to pick a fight. 2 times I was killed after 1.62 by scouts.  The scout seems to get better and better while hunters get worse and worse. <br>
<br>
In large battles skalds who fall are often passed over for tanks for rezes first and when resed often I get the cheep rez now instead of one where I can fight back without rest. I have gone to carrying potions to make up for my short comings and proc’s on throw away weaponds that have more range then my normal spells, which is very disheartening.<br>
<br>
In the last; day long battle I fought in, I spend well over 1 plat in proc’s and potions to supplement what I use to get from the groups I was in and add some spells at range so I felt I was adding to the fight. <br>
<br>
I think unless the &quot;powers that be&quot; fix my class I will move games to Planetside or SWG I just don’t like the monthly changes of our class system and the building of new toons because of it.  free 30 or no free 30<br>
<br>
Hazardous<br>
<br>
