<br>
Logged on at hib gate in Odin's one night and saw an unstealthed NS standing there in a corner. Of course I was unbuffed at the moment but I had IP up and would get the jump so I decided to go for it. Thought I'd start off with a DD, DD, Assault and then snare and run like the kobold I am but one DD was resisted, the assault missed and the snare didnt land. Doh!<br>
Tried with a mez but that one didn't seem to stick either. So there I was, fighting the best I could with a NS. Managed to get him to about 70% at least even tho I blew IP. Felt kinda nice after that. Took me a week or so before I even thought about logging on again.. Not because I lost but because it felt it was no way that I ever could beat a (hopefully) buffed NS in face up melee..<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I think the fondest memory I have of 'lil Gnishy was when he and the old and slow berserker Serion was roaming Odin's and jumped and killed four albs at AG. I beleive there were two tanks there, one cleric and some caster. We had both used up our IP and FA. He also blew his Purge in that battle. It was one of those battles when you feel like your certain to die a hundered times but manage to make it and take them all out instead.<br>
We met in RL a few days later and talked about that incident. Turned out we both had a hard time coming out of that trip afterwards.. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Of course he did his 600+ swings on the poor things while I was swinging away at some 150's but still.. It was a night to remember.. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyway, today I canceled my account after playing Gnish for a year and a half. It feels kinda strange but since I have lost interest in playing there is no point in paying Mythic any money either. I will of course be watching the progress of the game and of the skald class and hopefully one day return.<br>
Rosie, you do good! The skald community is lucky to have a TL like yourself!<br>
<br>
