Percival <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ororo7>Ororo7</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/19/03 3:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=640.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RvR experiences of Skalds</span><hr size=1> Nice stories.  But you were both extremely lucky that your enemies did not have Purge up.  The second story, where you landed the second mez, means 20 seconds passed before the other two were aware that you were killing one?<br>
<br>
As a RR6 skald, I faced a RR2 blademaster.  It was a group on group battle.  I have no doubt we were both fully buffed.  In the 30 seconds it took him to kill my healer, I was free to dd/dd/axe him from behind (he was mez immune).  I had 4 misses due to evade, and landed 2 axe blows for 200 (-100).  When he turned to face me, he ripped me apart in less than 10 seconds.<br>
<br>
Against any Friar 1-on-1, if I do anything besides run away, I am dead.  Friars kill fast.  And they evade most swings.<br>
<br>
The worst RvR happens again and again.  It happened last night just past MMG.  We exit MMG with a group of 8, and a group of Hibs swoop down.  Our healer mezzes, they group purge and mez most of us (or they win CC off the bat).  The MoC PBAoE enchanter rushes up.  I purge mez, and I am promptly stunned as I try and back off from death.  3 casts of pbaoe later, 600x3, less than 5 seconds, and 6 of us are dead.  The cast time on a fully buffed caster is now less than 2 seconds now that stat caps from buffs can shoot above 300.  You might say he is done for 30 minutes.  Well, sure, but it takes 15 minutes to get back, and they have 3 chanters per group, so they can kill us again and again all night.<br>
<br>
When we run with 3 skalds, which is rare but happens, none of us run Dam Add.  Most perceive it as worthless.  We run speed and 2 resist songs.<br>
<br>
If I can not argue for light tank status, i.e. enough melee skill to hit a R2 BM from behind or enough to matter in a battle, then at least give me some support tools that make a difference.  Once a battle starts, none of our songs matter.  I would trade all songs except speed for the ablative chant.<br>
<br>
