<br>
At the time I recall a number of fun RvR experiences.  Once at HMG in OG, I was running to suicide and a celt Bard and Champ duo came running through at the same time.  I waved, and kept going, but saw them turn and come after me.  On the other side of HMG, I mezzed Champ, and Bard for some reason started running from me—maybe was a bot duo played by 1 person, but both were RR5 at the time and I was probably RR4.  Champ did not purge, and I snared Bard and followed him DD’ing and hitting him in the back until he dropped…maybe he thought he’d survive until Champ broke free, or thought he would get a burst of speed in and get out of range, dunno.  Then I turn to Champ, he fights back.  Toe to toe fight, I am out of endo after getting some back with a bounty potion after Bard dropped.  I use some snare to buy time and so forth, I had high parry spec at time and no IP, but finally dropped him, got about 1800 rps from that little battle.<br>
<br>
Another fun spot was the zone wall going from Beno toward Pennine, there frequently would be a stealther right along rim of zone as I ran through, usually would drop them if they were just sitting there waiting for me to go past.  FS was a huge amount of fun, often would find people running along road to ambush, had some good fights.  Also, Alb dungeon HoC was a great spot, could have some fun and usually drop someone even if a group would come through, occasionally more if I waited until they were on a mob!<br>
<br>
Now with respec to include IP/Purge, lesser parry, game changes, I rarely solo by choice…there are classes I used to be able to have long fights with that slap me down regardless of what I do.  Players of most classes with a name I recognize, unfortunately, are encounters I avoid many times, whereas I jump in on any class with a new name in hopes they don’t know what they’re doing.  This can be a mistake. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
So most of my RvR is in groups now, and most of my groups are with guild or friends I have played with for a year or more and so I can’t comment on whether group invites come a skald's way very much these days.  However, I am usually /assisting in order to have much impact aside from interrupting or dropping someone with a sliver of health left.  If I get caught alone while others are working elsewhere, I am an easy target because my defense has become laughable versus so many classes who /evade and /parry me like hell while I am standing there waiting for another miss with my 2H.  With 202 Cha and 46 BS, my DDs have still continually declined in effectiveness.<br>
<br>
My favorite thing in group RvR early in my career was the use of speed to get into the enemy backfield and take out casters.  Now, I don’t for two reasons:  1)  speed is interrupted by so many things now—I imagine if a Hib inside Hibernia kills a water beetle, a skald somewhere has his speed interrupted; 2)  even with maxed magic resists, multiple casters mean I interrupt one and the others kill me—they don’t even have to get melee on me anymore.  I also used to be able to run quickly to the back of a pack and then pull an enemy who would /stick me back to our tanks.  Now, I die before I get close to help.  <br>
<br>
I used to use speed to run down and finish an enemy fleeing a group encounter.  Now, if I don’t have help, this is typically a poor decision.   I used to hit and crit well with my melee solo vs. rogues (MoPain II, was III at one point)…now they hit too hard and too often for an unbuffed skald, especially, to do much good.  Purge and IP are down, odds are poor.  <br>
<br>
What I miss most, perhaps, is being a priority target…it was fun running with a great healer or two who would key on me as I was hit by 2 or 3 opponents and being one of the last to stand.  Now, when I am one of the last standing, I believe it is because they know they can leave me ‘til last because I am less of a threat than most other classes.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I miss being able to get on a target hitting our healer/caster and actually giving him a reason to turn around and deal with me before killing my teammate.  I miss kiting.  I miss…<br>
<br>
Well, sorry this wasn’t all RvR stories as requested, but I’ve never posted much here and thought I'd share.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Hope we get more reason to play our class soon.<br>
